  "text": "Successful treatment of esophageal lung depends on how much of the lung is affected and the nature of the associated congenital anomalies. Resection and reimplantation of the anomalous airway into the trachea can be considered in some cases. However, pneumonectomy performed via a thoracotomy without cardiopulmonary bypass may be safer than bronchial reconstruction in patients with severe lung hypoplasia [CITATION_1] .",
